First, we need to find the intersection of sets A and B (A ∩ B). The intersection of two sets contains all the elements that are common to both sets.

A ∩ B = {2, 3}

Now, we need to find the Cartesian product of (A ∩ B) and {5}. The Cartesian product of two sets is the set of all ordered pairs (a, b) where a is an element of the first set and b is an element of the second set.

(A ∩ B) × {5} = {(2, 5), (3, 5)}
